Walter Pym (actor) https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Walter_Pym_(actor) 0 Walter Pym (7 April 1905– 22 January 1980) was an Australian actor and producer best known for his extensive experience in radio, during the 1930s and 40s, he featured in film and television appearances, making his screen debut in 1943. He was born in the Sydney suburb of Petersham in 1905 and died in Prahran, Melbourne, aged 74 in 1980, he was married to Ivy Ray from 1928 until 1963, and had one son.
